==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Blazer
<hw>Blaz"er</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who spreads
reports or blazes matters abroad.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Blazers</xex> of
crime.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Blazer</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Blazer
<hw>Blaz"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Anything
that blazes or glows, as with heat or flame.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A light jacket, usually of wool or silk and of a
bright color, for wear at tennis, cricket, or other sport.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The dish used when cooking directly over the flame
of a chafing-dish lamp, or the coals of a brasier.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Blazing</ent>⟦br⟧
